txt.en: 'The shadows barring the door begin to weaken...'
'Ah, you have come!'
'I see the allure of confronting me proved too tempting.'
'None but the servants of the Great Eye may cross this bridge!'
'I remember you, [placeholder], even if you have forgotten me!'
'When last I saw you, I swore to become a great Wizard in the East!'
The Dome of Stars
'Yet, my quest was naught but folly, you see...'
'...for that old fool Saruman is defeated and left to rot in his tower!'
'I bet even he did not suspect such incredible feats from one so lowly...'
'Once a servant - now a Lord!'
'What have you done to my flock?!'
'You have always stood in my way, but not this time!'
'I cannot allow you to do this, [placeholder].'
'Latu gadhumúrz bagu!'
'The Eye has no use for cowards, Harad-filth!'
'The door to the Hall of the Osgiliath-stone flies open with a shriek!'
'You shall only find death in Osgiliath!'
'You may cast off these robes, but ever shall I escape death! The fate of Minas Tirith cannot be undone...'
'Enough!'
'I yield this worthless city to you!'
'Your memories burden you, [placeholder]. I shall free you of them!'
'But know this, [placeholder]...'
'Middle-earth shall still be mine!'
'The gate in the north-eastern corner of Rómendacil's Square thunders open...'
'How'd these little ones sneak over here? They're like the ones in the cloaks!'
'I wonder if they smash as well as 'em!'
'My birds! My precious crebain! Come back!'
'Feed, my pet! They have nowhere to run!'
'He has gone wild, brothers! We must subdue him... ready the poisons!'
'Is this some joke? You are fools to have come here!'
'On your feet! Rest waits for death!'
'The door to the Hall of the Osgiliath-stone is barred by the fell power of the Black-guard Door-wardens.'
'Death is all that awaits those that defy the might of Sauron!'
'That's far enough, [placeholder]-filth!'
'Long have you battled and much have you sacrificed to gaze upon your doom!'
'You abandoned me to death, [placeholder]! Has your courage failed you again?'
'Look below! The Scourge of Umbar and the host of Minas Morgul shall lay waste to Minas Tirith!'
'None can defy the Masters and live!'
'Now do you understand the true meaning of terror?'
'Yet that is not your fate, mortals... you shall be the first to die!'
'Kill them all!'
'He'll kill us all, you fools!'
